# Competitive Exam Website Implementation Plan

The objective is to replace the default Vite boilerplate with a modern, high-quality, and visually stunning landing page for competitive exam preparation.

## User Review Required

> [!CAUTION]
> The existing Vite boilerplate files ([main.js](file:///d:/AIFS/src/main.js), [style.css](file:///d:/AIFS/src/style.css), [counter.js](file:///d:/AIFS/src/counter.js)) will be completely replaced by the new website structure. Please confirm that it is okay to overwrite these files.
> We'll be using Vanilla JavaScript and CSS as per the current setup, rather than switching to a framework like React, to keep it lightweight while ensuring a premium look and feel.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Files
#### [MODIFY] [index.html](file:///d:/AIFS/index.html)
- Add Google Fonts (Inter and Outfit).
- Add FontAwesome for icons.
- Add SEO meta tags and update the `<title>`.
- Set up the root `<div id="app"></div>`.

#### [MODIFY] [main.js](file:///d:/AIFS/src/main.js)
- Rewrite the entire file to inject the HTML structure into `#app`.
- Structure will include:
  - **Navbar**: Sticky header with logo and navigation links.
  - **Hero Section**: Engaging headline, dynamic gradient text, and primary Call-To-Action (CTA).
  - **Features Section**: Grid layout highlighting platform benefits (e.g., Mock Tests, Expert Faculty, Real-time Analytics) with icons and micro-animations.
  - **Popular Exams Section**: Cards representing different competitive exams (e.g., JEE, NEET, UPSC).
  - **Footer**: Simple footer with copyright and links.
- Add JavaScript logic for mobile menu toggling and simple interactions.

#### [DELETE] [counter.js](file:///d:/AIFS/src/counter.js)
- Remove this boilerplate file as it is no longer needed.

### Design System & Styling
#### [MODIFY] [style.css](file:///d:/AIFS/src/style.css)
- Implement a modern, premium design system using CSS variables (`:root`).
- Use a color palette: Vibrant Primary (e.g., Indigo/Blue), Dark accents, and clean off-white backgrounds.
- Add utility classes for layout (flexbox, grid), typography, and spacing.
- Implement micro-animations (hover effects on buttons and cards, smooth transitions).
- Ensure full responsiveness using CSS media queries.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
Currently, there are no tests set up in the Vite boilerplate. We will rely on manual visual verification.

### Manual Verification
1. I will run the Vite development server using `npm run dev` in the terminal.
2. I will use the browser tool to load `http://localhost:5173` and capture screenshots.
3. I will verify that the layout is visually appealing, responsive, and matches the premium design requirements.
4. I will verify interactions like hover states and mobile menu toggling.
